definition.value: A populated place. A village on the northern shore of Lake Balaton on the Tihany Peninsula.
A province of the Netherlands, located in the central eastern part of the country.
A populated place.

A province of the Netherlands, and is located in the center of the country. It is bordered by the Eemmeer in the north, Gelderland in the east, the river Rhine in the south, South Holland in the west, and North Holland in the northwest.
A populated place.

A state on the tropical Malabar Coast of southwestern India. To its east and northeast, Kerala borders Tamil Nadu and Karnataka; to its west and south lie the Indian Ocean islands of Lakshadweep and the Maldives, respectively. Kerala nearly envelops Mahe, a coastal exclave of Pondicherry. It is divided into 14 Districts which are further divided into 62 taluks, 1453 revenue villages and 1007 Gram panchayats.

A province of the Netherlands, located in the west of the country on the North Sea coast. Neighbouring provinces are Zeeland to the southwest, North Brabant to the southeast, Gelderland to the east, Utrecht to the northeast and North Holland to the north.
A province of the Netherlands, located in the south of the country, bordered by Belgium in the south, the Maas River in the north, Limburg in the east and Zeeland in the west.
A populated place.
A populated place.

The southernmost of the twelve provinces of the Netherlands. It is located in the southeastern part of the country and bordered by the province of Gelderland to the north, Germany to the east, Belgium to the south and part of the west, and the Dutch province of North Brabant partly to the west. Its capital is Maastricht.
A province situated on the North Sea in the northwest part of the Netherlands.

The northeasternmost province of the Netherlands. In the east it borders the German state of Niedersachsen (districts of Leer and Emsland), in the south Drenthe, in the west Friesland and in the north the Wadden Sea.

A province of The Netherlands. The capital city is Assen. It is bordered by Overijssel to the south, Friesland to the west, Groningen to the north, and Germany (districts of Emsland and Bentheim) to the east.

A province of the Netherlands. Located in the centre of the country, at the location of the former Zuiderzee, the province was established on 1986-01-01; the twelfth province of the country, with Lelystad as its capital.
A province in the north of the Netherlands.
A province of the Netherlands in the central eastern part of the country.
A province of the Netherlands. The province, located in the south-west of the country, consists of a number of islands and a strip bordering Belgium.

A canton located in west-central Switzerland and the city of Berne is its capital. It borders the Canton of Jura and the Canton of Solothurn to the north. To the west lie the Canton of Neuchatel, the Canton of Fribourg and Vaud. To the south lies the Valais. East of the canton of Berne lie the cantons of Uri, Nidwalden, Obwalden, Lucerne and Aargau. As of 2004-04, there are 398 municipalities of the canton of Berne within 26 administrative districts.
The Bundesstadt of Switzerland.

A canton of Switzerland that is located in the northeast of Switzerland and the city of Zu rich is its capital. The canton of Zu rich is situated north of the Alps. Its neighbouring cantons are Schaffhausen to the north, Aargau to the west, the cantons of Zug and Schwyz to the south and the cantons of Thurgau and St. Gallen to the east. Most of the Lake Zu rich is located within the canton. The Canton of Zu rich is divided into 12 districts (German: Bezirke). These districts are further subdivided into 171 municipalities (Politische Gemeinden).
A populated place. A city in the Canton of Zurich, Switzerland. It is situated where the river Limmat issues from the north-western end of Lake Zurich.

One of the 26 cantons of Switzerland. The city of Basel and the municipalities of Bettingen and Riehen form its territory. The canton of Basel-City is located in the north of Switzerland. It borders Germany and France to the north, Basel-Landschaft to the south.
A city located in north-west Switzerland on the river Rhine.
An unincorporated territory of the United States.
lat_lon: 13deg27minN, 144deg47minE.
A coastal city situated on the eastern shores of Gulf Saint Vincent, on the Adelaide Plains, north of the Fleurieu Peninsula, between the Gulf Saint Vincent and the low-lying Mount Lofty Ranges.
A populated place. A city in South East Queensland, Australia.

One of Rwanda's five provinces. It was created in early 2006-01. North Province comprises most of the former provinces of Ruhengeri and Byumba, along with northern portions of Kigali Rural. It is divided into the districts of Burera, Byumba, Gakenke, Ruhengeri, and Rulindo.

One of Rwanda's five provinces. It was created in early 2006-01. South Province comprises the former provinces of Gikongoro, Gitarama, and Butare, and is divided into the districts of Butare, Gatagara, Gikongoro, Gisagara, Gitarama, Kamonyi, Kyanza, and Nyaruguru. The capital city of South Province is Nyanza.
One of Rwanda's five provinces. It was created in early 2006-01. East Province comprises the former provinces of Kibungo and Umutara, most of Kigali Rural, and part of Byumba.

One of Rwanda's five provinces. It was created in early 2006-01. West Province comprises the former provinces of Cyangugu, Gisenyi, Kibuye, and a small portion of Ruhengeri. It is divided into the districts of Cyangugu, Gasiza, Gisenyi, Kibuye, Ngororero, Nyamasheke, and Rutsiro.

One of Rwanda's five provinces, and is coterminous with Kigali City. It was created in early 2006-01. Kigali Province comprises parts of the former province of Kigali Rural and the city of Kigali, and is divided into the districts of Gasabo, Kicukiro, and Nyarugenge.
The capital and largest city of Rwanda.
A small town in Mpumalanga Province, South Africa.
Also: Belfast in Limpopo, South Africa.
A populated place. A town situated on a tributary of the Mkhomazi River in the midlands of KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa.

The capital and largest city of Indonesia. It was formerly known as Sunda Kalapa (397-1527), Jayakarta (1527-1619), Batavia (1619-1942), and Djakarta (1942-1972). Located on the northwest coast of the Java Island. Its metropolitan area is called Jabodetabek and is part of an even larger Jakarta-Bandung megalopolis.
A province of Indonesia with the provincial capital at Denpasar towards the south of the island. Located on the island of Bali and satellite islands.
The capital region of Indonesia.
One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is the city of Dar es Salaam itself.
The largest city in Tanzania.

The capital of the Tunisian Republic and also the Tunis Governorate. Situated on a large Mediterranean gulf, (the Gulf of Tunis), behind the Lake of Tunis and the port of La Goulette (Halq al Wadi), the city extends along the coastal plain and the hills that surround it.
The capital of HokkaidoPrefecture. Located in the southwest part of Ishikari Plain and the alluvial fan of the Toyohira River, a tributary stream of the Ishikari River.
The largest city of Thailand.

The capital of Bangladesh and the principal city of Dhaka District. It is located on the banks of the Buriganga River. It consists of seven principal thanas: Dhanmondi, Kotwali, Motijheel, Paltan, Ramna, Mohammadpur, Sutrapur, Tejgaon, and 14 auxiliary thanas: Gulshan, Lalbagh, Mirpur, Pallabi, Sabujbagh, Dhaka Cantonment, Demra, Hazaribagh, Shyampur, Badda, Kafrul, Kamrangir char, Khilgaon and Uttara.

An administrative division within Bangladesh. The capital and largest city is Dhaka. Dhaka Division bounds the Indian State of Meghalaya to the north, Barisal and Chittagong Divisions on the south, Sylhet Division to the east, Rajshahi and Khulna Divisions to the west.
